\cf5 \ulnone Global and private debating pages\
\

\fs26 \cf0 This is where all standard discussions and debates are on the site.\

\fs40 \cf5 \

\f1\b\fs26 \cf0 The difference between global and private
\f0\b0 \
\
The concept of having global and private debates on buzzZap is very important to understand. Essentially, every community have their own private content (debates, discussions, competitions, etc) that cannot be seen or viewed by anyone outside the community. However there is also the global content which anyone, from any community, can see. If you were to post a debate in the global section in the category \'93Law\'94 (for example), anyone on the site who visited the global section and went to the \'93Law\'94 category can see that debate. Whereas if it were posted in the private section, then only those in your community can see it.\
\

\f1\b Starting a debate
\f0\b0 \
\
Global and private debating works exactly the same when it comes to posting, discussing, etc. So, when it comes to starting a debate, visit the category page either in the global or private section, go to the category that fits the topic of your debate question best, and simply click "start a debate" at the top right of the page. Please note, if you are a new user, your posts and debates will not become visible to any other users immediately until your community leader approves it. Once your reputation reaches 20, you will be able to post freely without the approval phase. This is to confirm that BuzzZap can trust each new user to post appropriate and responsible content.
\fs40 \ul \
\

\f1\b\fs26 \ulnone Discussion
\f0\b0 \
\
Getting involved in a debate is very easy. Once you have chosen a debate to view (choose private or global, choose a category, then choose a debate) you will see a thread of posts. To post an argument, go to the bottom of the page, and submit your argument. It is optional to vote. Each main argument posted will also have a thread of mini replies. This means you can directly address any main argument. The approval phase applies to posting arguments and comments as well if you reputation is under 20.
