\fs40 \cf5 \
Community groups page\
\

\fs26 \cf0 Groups are teams of users within communities. This page is simply to view all the groups within your community, and who is part of what group.\

\fs40 \cf5 \

\f1\b\fs26 \cf0 Starting a new group
\f0\b0 \
\
You cannot start a new group if you are already in one. In other words, you can only be in one group at a time. Any member can start a new group and invite other users to join, and if you started the group you will be the leader. \
\

\f1\b Accepting join invitations & leaving groups
\f0\b0 \
\
To leave a group go to the groups page, go to your group\'92s section, and by the group\'92s name click \'93leave group\'94. \
\
To accept an invitation to join a group, go to that group on the groups page and by the group\'92s name click \'93Accept invitation to join\'94. If you are already part of a group, you must leave that one first to join a new one.
