\fs40 \cf5 \
Community Manager Panel\

\fs26 \cf0 \
The Community manager is very important for the community leader. Especially if your community is a school. This section is strictly for the community leader to use, so other users cannot access the panel in any way.\
To access the manager, go to the link on the top right of the page on the menu bar. Here, you will see three different sections.\

\fs40 \cf5 \

\f1\b\fs26 \cf0 General management
\f0\b0 \
\
General management is for any basic community settings. At the moment, this is where you can post the community news which appears on every user\'92s home page in that community. More settings and options will be added to BuzzZap in the future.\

\fs40 \cf5 \

\f1\b\fs26 \cf0 User management
\f0\b0 \
\
This is where you can manipulate a user. If you need to ban, delete, etc a user then enter the user\'92s username into the user actions field, choose your action, then submit. \

\f1\b \
User actions
\f0\b0 \
\
-\ul Banning a user\ulnone : the user will no longer be able to access their account, until you unban them.\
-\ul Deleting a user\ulnone : the user\'92s account will be permanently deleted.\
-\ul Editing a user: \ulnone You can change a users name, password, etc.\
-\ul Turning on close moderation: \ulnone This will mean a user cannot post any content without going through the approval phase (when they try and post, the post will appear in content management for you to approve or delete before it is visible to other users).\
